        <item>
            <title>美大学研发全球最细无人机，直径不足 1 厘米、重量仅 0.021 克</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2025/04/07/uc-berkeley-engineers-create-worlds-smallest-wireless-flying-robot/fun-tech/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=uc-berkeley-engineers-create-worlds-smallest-wireless-flying-robot</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2025/04/07/uc-berkeley-engineers-create-worlds-smallest-wireless-flying-robot/fun-tech/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Oscar]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Mon, 07 Apr 2025 07:26:51 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[科技新闻]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[飞行机械人]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1301059</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>美国加州大学伯克利分校（University of California Berkeley，UC Berkeley）的科研团队成功研制出全球最小的无线飞行机械人。这款受蜜蜂启发的装置，直径不足 1 厘米，重量仅 21 毫克，能人手操控飞行路径。研究人员利用外部磁场供电及控制其飞行路径，展示其在人工授粉及探索狭小空间的潜力。团队计划进一步将其缩小至 1 毫米以内，并提升操控性能。</p><div class="epyt-video-wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy"  style="display: block; margin: 0px auto;"  id="_ytid_52059"  width="590" height="332"  data-origwidth="590" data-origheight="332" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/4teCe7-qqAo?enablejsapi=1&#038;autoplay=0&#038;cc_load_policy=0&#038;cc_lang_pref=&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;loop=0&#038;modestbranding=1&#038;rel=0&#038;fs=1&#038;playsinline=1&#038;autohide=1&#038;theme=light&#038;color=white&#038;controls=1&#038;" class="__youtube_prefs__  epyt-is-override  no-lazyload" title="YouTube player"  allow="fullscreen; accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen data-no-lazy="1" data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll=""></iframe></div><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1301063" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/20250321_drone_avl_0-2-694x463.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="463" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/20250321_drone_avl_0-2-694x463.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/20250321_drone_avl_0-2.jpg 1024w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲研发团队手持微型机械人合照，图片来源：UC Berkeley News</p><h2>技术突破与应用前景</h2><p>这款微型飞行机械人外形似小螺旋桨，内置两块微型磁铁，通过外部磁场驱动旋转起飞。据《Science Advances》于 2025 年 3 月 28 日刊登的论文，其尺寸比现有同类机械人小近三倍（对比 2.8 厘米）。研究团队指，其应用范围广泛，例如检查管道内部或协助农业授粉。美国国家科学基金会近期亦关注此技术，认为其或可用于环境监测，如追踪空气污染物。目前机械人需依赖强磁场操控，限制其灵活性。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1301061" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/20250321_drone_avl_0-1-387x580.jpg" alt="" width="387" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/20250321_drone_avl_0-1-387x580.jpg 387w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/20250321_drone_avl_0-1.jpg 600w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 387px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲机械人设计模仿蜜蜂飞行路径，图片来源：UC Berkeley News</p><h2>未来发展方向</h2><p>科研团队正努力克服现有局限，例如加入主动控制功能，让机械人能即时调整姿态及位置。据外媒《tech explore》报导，伯克利工程学院正探索以无线电波取代强磁场，减轻操控设备负担。此外团队亦开发其他仿生机械人，如蟑螂型及群体协作型，冀应用于微创手术等领域。这款微型飞行机械人标志著无人机技术的一大进步，其极小体积与潜在应用令人瞩目。随著技术完善，例如减弱磁场依赖及提升自主性，未来或见更多在医疗、农业及环境领域的突破。</p><p>资料来源：<a href="https://news.berkeley.edu/2025/03/28/uc-berkeley-engineers-create-worlds-smallest-wireless-flying-robot/">UC Berkeley News</a>、<a href="https://techxplore.com/news/2025-03-world-smallest-wireless-flying-robot.html?deviceType=desktop#google_vignette">Tech Explore</a></p><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2025/04/07/uc-berkeley-engineers-create-worlds-smallest-wireless-flying-robot/fun-tech/">美大学研发全球最细无人机，直径不足 1 厘米、重量仅 0.021 克</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
]]>
            </description>
